{
    "identity": "nprot-415",
    "title": "Tensin-PTBc expression and purification",
    "content": [
        {
            "header": "Introduction",
            "content": "Protocol describes expression and purificaton of PTB domain from tensin in bacterial culture."
        },
        {
            "header": "Reagents",
            "content": "pET15b-His-Tensin-PTBc \\(aa1653-1786)\r\n\n\nMW 15.5KD\r\n\n\nExt Coef 0.484 \\(or 7090 to get &#xB5;M)\r\n\n\n\r\n\n\n**Binding Buffer \\(High Salt)**\r\n\n\n5mM Imidazole\r\n\n\n500mM NaCl\r\n\n\n20mM Tris-HCl pH 7.9\r\n\n\n1mM DTT\r\n\n\n\r\n\n\n**Elution Buffer \\(Low Salt)**\r\n\n\n300mM Imidazole\r\n\n\n100mM NaCl\r\n\n\n20mM Tris-HCl pH 7.9\r\n\n\n1mM DTT\r\n\n\n\r\n\n\n**Wash Buffer \\(Low Salt)**\r\n\n\n30mM Imidazole\r\n\n\n100mM NaCl\r\n\n\n20mM Tris-HCl pH 7.9\r\n\n\n1mM DTT\r\n\n\n\r\n\n\n**Dialysis Buffer**\r\n\n\n20mM Tris-HCl pH 7.9\r\n\n\n100mM NaCl\r\n\n\n1mM DTT"
        },
        {
            "header": "Procedure",
            "content": "**Expression**\r\n\n\n1) 100ml o/n LB/amp culture\r\n\n\n2) Next day seed 700ml LB/amp with 100ml o/n culture, 37\u00b0C.\r\n\n\n3) Grow cells until OD600 = 0.6-1.2\r\n\n\n4) Induce with 1mM IPTG.  Grow for 3hr 37\u00b0C.\r\n\n\n5) Harvest 8krpm, 4 \u00b0C, 10min.\r\n\n\n6) Resuspend 800ml cell culture pellet in 20ml Ni-NTA binding buffer.  LN\n2\nfreeze.\r\n\n\n\r\n\n\n**Purification**\r\n\n\n1) Thaw 1L cells.  Add PI tablet w/o EDTA.  Add 2mM PMSF.\r\n\n\n2) Add 0.4mg/ml lysozyme.  Rock 15-30min until thick.\r\n\n\n3) Add 10mM MgCl\n2\n.  Add 0.4\u00b5g/ml DNaseI.  Rock 15-30min until loose.\r\n\n\n4) Add 0.1% Tx-100.  Rock 15min.  Save 10\u00b5l for SDS-PAGE.\r\n\n\n5) Spin 16krpm, 4\u00b0C, 15min.  Save some supernatant and pellet for gel.\r\n\n\n6) Meanwhile, wash 2ml Ni-NTA beads with binding buffer.\r\n\n\n7) Load supernatant onto beads.\r\n\n\n8) Wash with 50ml binding buffer.\r\n\n\n9) Wash with 50ml wash buffer low salt.\r\n\n\n10) Elute with elution buffer low salt.\r\n\n\n11) Dialize into dialysis buffer while digesting off His tag with biotinylated thrombin.  Digest for 6hr RT.  Capture biotinylated thrombin with streptavidin agarose.\r\n\n\n12) Run SDS PAGE on purification.  Determine if need to do further purification on S75 or S200. Do a quick protein concentration check.  Concentrate if necessary."
        }
    ],
